1 //===- TwoAddressInstructionPass.cpp - Two-Address instruction pass -------===// ----

7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // This file implements the TwoAddress instruction pass which is used ----
10 // by most register allocators. Two-Address instructions are rewritten ----
11 // from: ----
12 // ----
13 // A = B op C ----
14 // ----
15 // to: ----
16 // ----
17 // A = B ----
18 // A op= C ----
19 // ----
20 // Note that if a register allocator chooses to use this pass, that it ----
21 // has to be capable of handling the non-SSA nature of these rewritten ----
22 // virtual registers. ----
23 // ----
24 // It is also worth noting that the duplicate operand of the two ----
25 // address instruction is removed. ----
26 // ----
27 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
28 ----

216 /// Check if there is a reversed copy chain from FromReg to ToReg: ----
217 /// %Tmp1 = copy %Tmp2; ----
218 /// %FromReg = copy %Tmp1; ----
219 /// %ToReg = add %FromReg ... ----
220 /// %Tmp2 = copy %ToReg; ----
221 /// MaxLen specifies the maximum length of the copy chain the func ----
222 /// can walk through. ----
223 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass::isRevCopyChain(Register FromReg, Register ToReg, 0
224 int Maxlen) { ----
225 Register TmpReg = FromReg; 0
226 for (int i = 0; i < Maxlen; i++) { 0
227 MachineInstr *Def = getSingleDef(TmpReg, MBB, MRI); 0
228 if (!Def || !Def->isCopy()) 0
229 return false; 0
230 ----
231 TmpReg = Def->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
232 ----
233 if (TmpReg == ToReg) 0
234 return true; 0
235 } ----
236 return false; 0
237 } ----

239 /// Return true if there are no intervening uses between the last instruction ----

242 /// by reference. ----
243 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass::noUseAfterLastDef(Register Reg, unsigned Dist, 0
244 unsigned &LastDef) { ----
245 LastDef = 0; 0
246 unsigned LastUse = Dist; 0

248 MachineInstr *MI = MO.getParent(); 0
249 if (MI->getParent() != MBB || MI->isDebugValue()) 0
250 continue; 0
251 DenseMap::iterator DI = DistanceMap.find(MI); 0
252 if (DI == DistanceMap.end()) 0
253 continue; 0
254 if (MO.isUse() && DI->second < LastUse) 0
255 LastUse = DI->second; 0
256 if (MO.isDef() && DI->second > LastDef) 0
257 LastDef = DI->second; 0
258 } ----
259 ----
260 return !(LastUse > LastDef && LastUse < Dist); 0
261 } ----

317 ----
318 /// Test if the given register value, which is used by the given ----
319 /// instruction, is killed by the given instruction. This looks through ----
320 /// coalescable copies to see if the original value is potentially not killed. ----
321 /// ----
322 /// For example, in this code: ----
323 /// ----
324 /// %reg1034 = copy %reg1024 ----
325 /// %reg1035 = copy killed %reg1025 ----
326 /// %reg1036 = add killed %reg1034, killed %reg1035 ----
327 /// ----
328 /// %reg1034 is not considered to be killed, since it is copied from a ----
329 /// register which is not killed. Treating it as not killed lets the ----
330 /// normal heuristics commute the (two-address) add, which lets ----
331 /// coalescing eliminate the extra copy. ----
332 /// ----
333 /// If allowFalsePositives is true then likely kills are treated as kills even ----
334 /// if it can't be proven that they are kills. ----
335 static bool isKilled(MachineInstr &MI, Register Reg, 0
336 const MachineRegisterInfo *MRI, const TargetInstrInfo *TII, ----
337 LiveIntervals *LIS, bool allowFalsePositives) { ----
338 MachineInstr *DefMI = &MI; 0
339 while (true) { ----
340 // All uses of physical registers are likely to be kills. ----
341 if (Reg.isPhysical() && (allowFalsePositives || MRI->hasOneUse(Reg))) 0
342 return true; 0
343 if (!isPlainlyKilled(DefMI, Reg, LIS)) 0
344 return false; 0
345 if (Reg.isPhysical()) 0
346 return true; 0
347 MachineRegisterInfo::def_iterator Begin = MRI->def_begin(Reg); 0
348 // If there are multiple defs, we can't do a simple analysis, so just ----
349 // go with what the kill flag says. ----
350 if (std::next(Begin) != MRI->def_end()) 0
351 return true; 0
352 DefMI = Begin->getParent(); 0
353 bool IsSrcPhys, IsDstPhys; ----
354 Register SrcReg, DstReg; 0
355 // If the def is something other than a copy, then it isn't going to ----
356 // be coalesced, so follow the kill flag. ----
357 if (!isCopyToReg(*DefMI, TII, SrcReg, DstReg, IsSrcPhys, IsDstPhys)) 0
358 return true; 0
359 Reg = SrcReg; 0
360 } 0
361 } ----

528 /// Return true if it's potentially profitable to commute the two-address ----
529 /// instruction that's being processed. ----
530 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass::isProfitableToCommute(Register RegA, 0
531 Register RegB, ----
532 Register RegC, ----
533 MachineInstr *MI, ----
534 unsigned Dist) { ----
535 if (OptLevel == CodeGenOpt::None) 0
536 return false; 0
537 ----
538 // Determine if it's profitable to commute this two address instruction. In ----
539 // general, we want no uses between this instruction and the definition of ----
540 // the two-address register. ----
541 // e.g. ----
542 // %reg1028 = EXTRACT_SUBREG killed %reg1027, 1 ----
543 // %reg1029 = COPY %reg1028 ----
544 // %reg1029 = SHR8ri %reg1029, 7, implicit dead %eflags ----
545 // insert => %reg1030 = COPY %reg1028 ----
546 // %reg1030 = ADD8rr killed %reg1028, killed %reg1029, implicit dead %eflags ----
547 // In this case, it might not be possible to coalesce the second COPY ----
548 // instruction if the first one is coalesced. So it would be profitable to ----
549 // commute it: ----
550 // %reg1028 = EXTRACT_SUBREG killed %reg1027, 1 ----
551 // %reg1029 = COPY %reg1028 ----
552 // %reg1029 = SHR8ri %reg1029, 7, implicit dead %eflags ----
553 // insert => %reg1030 = COPY %reg1029 ----
554 // %reg1030 = ADD8rr killed %reg1029, killed %reg1028, implicit dead %eflags ----
555 ----
556 if (!isPlainlyKilled(MI, RegC, LIS)) 0
557 return false; 0
558 ----
559 // Ok, we have something like: ----
560 // %reg1030 = ADD8rr killed %reg1028, killed %reg1029, implicit dead %eflags ----
561 // let's see if it's worth commuting it. ----
562 ----
563 // Look for situations like this: ----
564 // %reg1024 = MOV r1 ----
565 // %reg1025 = MOV r0 ----
566 // %reg1026 = ADD %reg1024, %reg1025 ----
567 // r0 = MOV %reg1026 ----
568 // Commute the ADD to hopefully eliminate an otherwise unavoidable copy. ----
569 MCRegister ToRegA = getMappedReg(RegA, DstRegMap); 0
570 if (ToRegA) { 0
571 MCRegister FromRegB = getMappedReg(RegB, SrcRegMap); 0
572 MCRegister FromRegC = getMappedReg(RegC, SrcRegMap); 0
573 bool CompB = FromRegB && regsAreCompatible(FromRegB, ToRegA, TRI); 0
574 bool CompC = FromRegC && regsAreCompatible(FromRegC, ToRegA, TRI); 0
575 ----
576 // Compute if any of the following are true: ----
577 // -RegB is not tied to a register and RegC is compatible with RegA. ----
578 // -RegB is tied to the wrong physical register, but RegC is. ----
579 // -RegB is tied to the wrong physical register, and RegC isn't tied. ----
580 if ((!FromRegB && CompC) || (FromRegB && !CompB && (!FromRegC || CompC))) 0
581 return true; 0
582 // Don't compute if any of the following are true: ----
583 // -RegC is not tied to a register and RegB is compatible with RegA. ----
584 // -RegC is tied to the wrong physical register, but RegB is. ----
585 // -RegC is tied to the wrong physical register, and RegB isn't tied. ----
586 if ((!FromRegC && CompB) || (FromRegC && !CompC && (!FromRegB || CompB))) 0
587 return false; 0
588 } ----
589 ----
590 // If there is a use of RegC between its last def (could be livein) and this ----
591 // instruction, then bail. ----
592 unsigned LastDefC = 0; 0
593 if (!noUseAfterLastDef(RegC, Dist, LastDefC)) 0
594 return false; 0
595 ----
596 // If there is a use of RegB between its last def (could be livein) and this ----
597 // instruction, then go ahead and make this transformation. ----
598 unsigned LastDefB = 0; 0
599 if (!noUseAfterLastDef(RegB, Dist, LastDefB)) 0
600 return true; 0
601 ----
602 // Look for situation like this: ----
603 // %reg101 = MOV %reg100 ----
604 // %reg102 = ... ----
605 // %reg103 = ADD %reg102, %reg101 ----
606 // ... = %reg103 ... ----
607 // %reg100 = MOV %reg103 ----
608 // If there is a reversed copy chain from reg101 to reg103, commute the ADD ----
609 // to eliminate an otherwise unavoidable copy. ----
610 // FIXME: ----
611 // We can extend the logic further: If an pair of operands in an insn has ----
612 // been merged, the insn could be regarded as a virtual copy, and the virtual ----
613 // copy could also be used to construct a copy chain. ----
614 // To more generally minimize register copies, ideally the logic of two addr ----
615 // instruction pass should be integrated with register allocation pass where ----
616 // interference graph is available. ----
617 if (isRevCopyChain(RegC, RegA, MaxDataFlowEdge)) 0
618 return true; 0
619 ----
620 if (isRevCopyChain(RegB, RegA, MaxDataFlowEdge)) 0
621 return false; 0
622 ----
623 // Look for other target specific commute preference. ----
624 bool Commute; ----
625 if (TII->hasCommutePreference(*MI, Commute)) 0
626 return Commute; 0
627 ----
628 // Since there are no intervening uses for both registers, then commute ----
629 // if the def of RegC is closer. Its live interval is shorter. ----
630 return LastDefB && LastDefC && LastDefC > LastDefB; 0
631 } ----

633 /// Commute a two-address instruction and update the basic block, distance map, ----
634 /// and live variables if needed. Return true if it is successful. ----
635 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass::commuteInstruction(MachineInstr *MI, 0
636 unsigned DstIdx, ----
637 unsigned RegBIdx, ----
638 unsigned RegCIdx, ----
639 unsigned Dist) { ----
640 Register RegC = MI->getOperand(RegCIdx).getReg(); 0
641 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "2addr: COMMUTING : " << *MI); 0
642 MachineInstr *NewMI = TII->commuteInstruction(*MI, false, RegBIdx, RegCIdx); 0
643 ----
644 if (NewMI == nullptr) { 0
645 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "2addr: COMMUTING FAILED!\n"); 0
646 return false; 0
647 } ----
648 ----
649 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "2addr: COMMUTED TO: " << *NewMI); 0
650 assert(NewMI == MI && 0
651 "TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstruction() should not return a new " ----
652 "instruction unless it was requested."); ----
653 ----
654 // Update source register map. ----
655 MCRegister FromRegC = getMappedReg(RegC, SrcRegMap); 0
656 if (FromRegC) { 0
657 Register RegA = MI->getOperand(DstIdx).getReg(); 0
658 SrcRegMap[RegA] = FromRegC; 0
659 } ----
660 ----
661 return true; 0
662 } ----

664 /// Return true if it is profitable to convert the given 2-address instruction ----
665 /// to a 3-address one. ----
666 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass::isProfitableToConv3Addr(Register RegA, 0
667 Register RegB) { ----
668 // Look for situations like this: ----
669 // %reg1024 = MOV r1 ----
670 // %reg1025 = MOV r0 ----
671 // %reg1026 = ADD %reg1024, %reg1025 ----
672 // r2 = MOV %reg1026 ----
673 // Turn ADD into a 3-address instruction to avoid a copy. ----
674 MCRegister FromRegB = getMappedReg(RegB, SrcRegMap); 0
675 if (!FromRegB) 0
676 return false; 0
677 MCRegister ToRegA = getMappedReg(RegA, DstRegMap); 0
678 return (ToRegA && !regsAreCompatible(FromRegB, ToRegA, TRI)); 0
679 } ----

681 /// Convert the specified two-address instruction into a three address one. ----
682 /// Return true if this transformation was successful. ----
683 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass::convertInstTo3Addr( 0
684 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &mi, MachineBasicBlock::iterator &nmi, ----
685 Register RegA, Register RegB, unsigned &Dist) { ----
686 MachineInstrSpan MIS(mi, MBB); 0
687 MachineInstr *NewMI = TII->convertToThreeAddress(*mi, LV, LIS); 0
688 if (!NewMI) 0
689 return false; 0
690 ----
691 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "2addr: CONVERTING 2-ADDR: " << *mi); 0
692 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "2addr: TO 3-ADDR: " << *NewMI); 0
693 ----
694 // If the old instruction is debug value tracked, an update is required. ----
695 if (auto OldInstrNum = mi->peekDebugInstrNum()) { 0
696 assert(mi->getNumExplicitDefs() == 1); 0
697 assert(NewMI->getNumExplicitDefs() == 1); 0
698 ----
699 // Find the old and new def location. ----
700 unsigned OldIdx = mi->defs().begin()->getOperandNo(); 0
701 unsigned NewIdx = NewMI->defs().begin()->getOperandNo(); 0
702 ----
703 // Record that one def has been replaced by the other. ----
704 unsigned NewInstrNum = NewMI->getDebugInstrNum(); 0
705 MF->makeDebugValueSubstitution(std::make_pair(OldInstrNum, OldIdx), 0
706 std::make_pair(NewInstrNum, NewIdx)); ----
707 } ----
708 ----
709 MBB->erase(mi); // Nuke the old inst. 0
710 ----
711 for (MachineInstr &MI : MIS) 0
712 DistanceMap.insert(std::make_pair(&MI, Dist++)); 0
713 Dist--; 0
714 mi = NewMI; 0
715 nmi = std::next(mi); 0
716 ----
717 // Update source and destination register maps. ----
718 SrcRegMap.erase(RegA); 0
719 DstRegMap.erase(RegB); 0
720 return true; 0
721 } ----

801 /// If there is one more local instruction that reads 'Reg' and it kills 'Reg, ----
802 /// consider moving the instruction below the kill instruction in order to ----
803 /// eliminate the need for the copy. ----
804 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass::rescheduleMIBelowKill( 0
805 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &mi, MachineBasicBlock::iterator &nmi, ----
806 Register Reg) { ----
807 // Bail immediately if we don't have LV or LIS available. We use them to find ----
808 // kills efficiently. ----
809 if (!LV && !LIS) 0
810 return false; 0
811 ----
812 MachineInstr *MI = &*mi; 0
813 DenseMap::iterator DI = DistanceMap.find(MI); 0
814 if (DI == DistanceMap.end()) 0
815 // Must be created from unfolded load. Don't waste time trying this. ----
816 return false; 0
817 ----
818 MachineInstr *KillMI = nullptr; 0
819 if (LIS) { 0
820 LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(Reg); 0
821 assert(LI.end() != LI.begin() && 0
822 "Reg should not have empty live interval."); ----
823 ----
824 SlotIndex MBBEndIdx = LIS->getMBBEndIdx(MBB).getPrevSlot(); 0
825 LiveInterval::const_iterator I = LI.find(MBBEndIdx); 0
826 if (I != LI.end() && I->start < MBBEndIdx) 0
827 return false; 0
828 ----
829 --I; 0
830 KillMI = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(I->end); 0
831 } else { ----
832 KillMI = LV->getVarInfo(Reg).findKill(MBB); 0
833 } ----
834 if (!KillMI || MI == KillMI || KillMI->isCopy() || KillMI->isCopyLike()) 0
835 // Don't mess with copies, they may be coalesced later. ----
836 return false; 0
837 ----
838 if (KillMI->hasUnmodeledSideEffects() || KillMI->isCall() || 0
839 KillMI->isBranch() || KillMI->isTerminator()) 0
840 // Don't move pass calls, etc. ----
841 return false; 0
842 ----
843 Register DstReg; 0
844 if (isTwoAddrUse(*KillMI, Reg, DstReg)) 0
845 return false; 0
846 ----
847 bool SeenStore = true; 0
848 if (!MI->isSafeToMove(AA, SeenStore)) 0
849 return false; 0
850 ----
851 if (TII->getInstrLatency(InstrItins, *MI) > 1) 0
852 // FIXME: Needs more sophisticated heuristics. ----
853 return false; 0
854 ----
855 SmallVector Uses; 0
856 SmallVector Kills; 0
857 SmallVector Defs; 0
858 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI->operands()) { 0
859 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
860 continue; 0
861 Register MOReg = MO.getReg(); 0
862 if (!MOReg) 0
863 continue; 0
864 if (MO.isDef()) 0
865 Defs.push_back(MOReg); 0
866 else { ----
867 Uses.push_back(MOReg); 0
868 if (MOReg != Reg && isPlainlyKilled(MO, LIS)) 0
869 Kills.push_back(MOReg); 0
870 } ----
871 } ----
872 ----
873 // Move the copies connected to MI down as well. ----
874 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Begin = MI; 0
875 MachineBasicBlock::iterator AfterMI = std::next(Begin); 0
876 MachineBasicBlock::iterator End = AfterMI; 0
877 while (End != MBB->end()) { 0
878 End = skipDebugInstructionsForward(End, MBB->end()); 0
879 if (End->isCopy() && regOverlapsSet(Defs, End->getOperand(1).getReg(), TRI)) 0
880 Defs.push_back(End->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
881 else ----
882 break; 0
883 ++End; 0
884 } ----
885 ----
886 // Check if the reschedule will not break dependencies. ----
887 unsigned NumVisited = 0; 0
888 MachineBasicBlock::iterator KillPos = KillMI; 0
889 ++KillPos; 0
890 for (MachineInstr &OtherMI : make_range(End, KillPos)) { 0
891 // Debug or pseudo instructions cannot be counted against the limit. ----
892 if (OtherMI.isDebugOrPseudoInstr()) 0
893 continue; 0
894 if (NumVisited > 10) // FIXME: Arbitrary limit to reduce compile time cost. 0
895 return false; 0
896 ++NumVisited; 0
897 if (OtherMI.hasUnmodeledSideEffects() || OtherMI.isCall() || 0
898 OtherMI.isBranch() || OtherMI.isTerminator()) 0
899 // Don't move pass calls, etc. ----
900 return false; 0
901 for (const MachineOperand &MO : OtherMI.operands()) { 0
902 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
903 continue; 0
904 Register MOReg = MO.getReg(); 0
905 if (!MOReg) 0
906 continue; 0
907 if (MO.isDef()) { 0
908 if (regOverlapsSet(Uses, MOReg, TRI)) 0
909 // Physical register use would be clobbered. ----
910 return false; 0
911 if (!MO.isDead() && regOverlapsSet(Defs, MOReg, TRI)) 0
912 // May clobber a physical register def. ----
913 // FIXME: This may be too conservative. It's ok if the instruction ----
914 // is sunken completely below the use. ----
915 return false; 0
916 } else { ----
917 if (regOverlapsSet(Defs, MOReg, TRI)) 0
918 return false; 0
919 bool isKill = isPlainlyKilled(MO, LIS); 0
920 if (MOReg != Reg && ((isKill && regOverlapsSet(Uses, MOReg, TRI)) || 0
921 regOverlapsSet(Kills, MOReg, TRI))) 0
922 // Don't want to extend other live ranges and update kills. ----
923 return false; 0
924 if (MOReg == Reg && !isKill) 0
925 // We can't schedule across a use of the register in question. ----
926 return false; 0
927 // Ensure that if this is register in question, its the kill we expect. ----
928 assert((MOReg != Reg || &OtherMI == KillMI) && 0
929 "Found multiple kills of a register in a basic block"); ----
930 } ----
931 } ----
932 } ----
933 ----
934 // Move debug info as well. ----
935 while (Begin != MBB->begin() && std::prev(Begin)->isDebugInstr()) 0
936 --Begin; 0
937 ----
938 nmi = End; 0
939 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPos = KillPos; 0
940 if (LIS) { 0
941 // We have to move the copies (and any interleaved debug instructions) ----
942 // first so that the MBB is still well-formed when calling handleMove(). ----
943 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = AfterMI; MBBI != End;) { 0
944 auto CopyMI = MBBI++; 0
945 MBB->splice(InsertPos, MBB, CopyMI); 0
946 if (!CopyMI->isDebugOrPseudoInstr()) 0
947 LIS->handleMove(*CopyMI); 0
948 InsertPos = CopyMI; 0
949 } ----
950 End = std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)); 0
951 } ----
952 ----
953 // Copies following MI may have been moved as well. ----
954 MBB->splice(InsertPos, MBB, Begin, End); 0
955 DistanceMap.erase(DI); 0
956 ----
957 // Update live variables ----
958 if (LIS) { 0
959 LIS->handleMove(*MI); 0
960 } else { ----
961 LV->removeVirtualRegisterKilled(Reg, *KillMI); 0
962 LV->addVirtualRegisterKilled(Reg, *MI); 0
963 } ----
964 ----
965 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\trescheduled below kill: " << *KillMI); 0
966 return true; 0
967 } 0

969 /// Return true if the re-scheduling will put the given instruction too close ----
970 /// to the defs of its register dependencies. ----
971 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass::isDefTooClose(Register Reg, unsigned Dist, 0
972 MachineInstr *MI) { ----
973 for (MachineInstr &DefMI : MRI->def_instructions(Reg)) { 0
974 if (DefMI.getParent() != MBB || DefMI.isCopy() || DefMI.isCopyLike()) 0
975 continue; 0
976 if (&DefMI == MI) 0
977 return true; // MI is defining something KillMI uses 0
978 DenseMap::iterator DDI = DistanceMap.find(&DefMI); 0
979 if (DDI == DistanceMap.end()) 0
980 return true; // Below MI 0
981 unsigned DefDist = DDI->second; 0
982 assert(Dist > DefDist && "Visited def already?"); 0
983 if (TII->getInstrLatency(InstrItins, DefMI) > (Dist - DefDist)) 0
984 return true; 0
985 } ----
986 return false; 0
987 } ----

989 /// If there is one more local instruction that reads 'Reg' and it kills 'Reg, ----
990 /// consider moving the kill instruction above the current two-address ----
991 /// instruction in order to eliminate the need for the copy. ----
992 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass::rescheduleKillAboveMI( 0
993 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &mi, MachineBasicBlock::iterator &nmi, ----
994 Register Reg) { ----
995 // Bail immediately if we don't have LV or LIS available. We use them to find ----
996 // kills efficiently. ----
997 if (!LV && !LIS) 0
998 return false; 0
999 ----
1000 MachineInstr *MI = &*mi; 0
1001 DenseMap::iterator DI = DistanceMap.find(MI); 0
1002 if (DI == DistanceMap.end()) 0
1003 // Must be created from unfolded load. Don't waste time trying this. ----
1004 return false; 0
1005 ----
1006 MachineInstr *KillMI = nullptr; 0
1007 if (LIS) { 0
1008 LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(Reg); 0
1009 assert(LI.end() != LI.begin() && 0
1010 "Reg should not have empty live interval."); ----
1011 ----
1012 SlotIndex MBBEndIdx = LIS->getMBBEndIdx(MBB).getPrevSlot(); 0
1013 LiveInterval::const_iterator I = LI.find(MBBEndIdx); 0
1014 if (I != LI.end() && I->start < MBBEndIdx) 0
1015 return false; 0
1016 ----
1017 --I; 0
1018 KillMI = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(I->end); 0
1019 } else { ----
1020 KillMI = LV->getVarInfo(Reg).findKill(MBB); 0
1021 } ----
1022 if (!KillMI || MI == KillMI || KillMI->isCopy() || KillMI->isCopyLike()) 0
1023 // Don't mess with copies, they may be coalesced later. ----
1024 return false; 0
1025 ----
1026 Register DstReg; 0
1027 if (isTwoAddrUse(*KillMI, Reg, DstReg)) 0
1028 return false; 0
1029 ----
1030 bool SeenStore = true; 0
1031 if (!KillMI->isSafeToMove(AA, SeenStore)) 0
1032 return false; 0
1033 ----
1034 SmallVector Uses; 0
1035 SmallVector Kills; 0
1036 SmallVector Defs; 0
1037 SmallVector LiveDefs; 0
1038 for (const MachineOperand &MO : KillMI->operands()) { 0
1039 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1040 continue; 0
1041 Register MOReg = MO.getReg(); 0
1042 if (MO.isUse()) { 0
1043 if (!MOReg) 0
1044 continue; 0
1045 if (isDefTooClose(MOReg, DI->second, MI)) 0
1046 return false; 0
1047 bool isKill = isPlainlyKilled(MO, LIS); 0
1048 if (MOReg == Reg && !isKill) 0
1049 return false; 0
1050 Uses.push_back(MOReg); 0
1051 if (isKill && MOReg != Reg) 0
1052 Kills.push_back(MOReg); 0
1053 } else if (MOReg.isPhysical()) { 0
1054 Defs.push_back(MOReg); 0
1055 if (!MO.isDead()) 0
1056 LiveDefs.push_back(MOReg); 0
1057 } ----
1058 } ----
1059 ----
1060 // Check if the reschedule will not break depedencies. ----
1061 unsigned NumVisited = 0; 0
1062 for (MachineInstr &OtherMI : 0
1063 make_range(mi, MachineBasicBlock::iterator(KillMI))) { 0
1064 // Debug or pseudo instructions cannot be counted against the limit. ----
1065 if (OtherMI.isDebugOrPseudoInstr()) 0
1066 continue; 0
1067 if (NumVisited > 10) // FIXME: Arbitrary limit to reduce compile time cost. 0
1068 return false; 0
1069 ++NumVisited; 0
1070 if (OtherMI.hasUnmodeledSideEffects() || OtherMI.isCall() || 0
1071 OtherMI.isBranch() || OtherMI.isTerminator()) 0
1072 // Don't move pass calls, etc. ----
1073 return false; 0
1074 SmallVector OtherDefs; 0
1075 for (const MachineOperand &MO : OtherMI.operands()) { 0
1076 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1077 continue; 0
1078 Register MOReg = MO.getReg(); 0
1079 if (!MOReg) 0
1080 continue; 0
1081 if (MO.isUse()) { 0
1082 if (regOverlapsSet(Defs, MOReg, TRI)) 0
1083 // Moving KillMI can clobber the physical register if the def has ----
1084 // not been seen. ----
1085 return false; 0
1086 if (regOverlapsSet(Kills, MOReg, TRI)) 0
1087 // Don't want to extend other live ranges and update kills. ----
1088 return false; 0
1089 if (&OtherMI != MI && MOReg == Reg && !isPlainlyKilled(MO, LIS)) 0
1090 // We can't schedule across a use of the register in question. ----
1091 return false; 0
1092 } else { ----
1093 OtherDefs.push_back(MOReg); 0
1094 } ----
1095 } ----
1096 ----
1097 for (unsigned i = 0, e = OtherDefs.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1098 Register MOReg = OtherDefs[i]; 0
1099 if (regOverlapsSet(Uses, MOReg, TRI)) 0
1100 return false; 0
1101 if (MOReg.isPhysical() && regOverlapsSet(LiveDefs, MOReg, TRI)) 0
1102 return false; 0
1103 // Physical register def is seen. ----
1104 llvm::erase_value(Defs, MOReg); 0
1105 } ----
1106 } 0
1107 ----
1108 // Move the old kill above MI, don't forget to move debug info as well. ----
1109 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPos = mi; 0
1110 while (InsertPos != MBB->begin() && std::prev(InsertPos)->isDebugInstr()) 0
1111 --InsertPos; 0
1112 MachineBasicBlock::iterator From = KillMI; 0
1113 MachineBasicBlock::iterator To = std::next(From); 0
1114 while (std::prev(From)->isDebugInstr()) 0
1115 --From; 0
1116 MBB->splice(InsertPos, MBB, From, To); 0
1117 ----
1118 nmi = std::prev(InsertPos); // Backtrack so we process the moved instr. 0
1119 DistanceMap.erase(DI); 0
1120 ----
1121 // Update live variables ----
1122 if (LIS) { 0
1123 LIS->handleMove(*KillMI); 0
1124 } else { ----
1125 LV->removeVirtualRegisterKilled(Reg, *KillMI); 0
1126 LV->addVirtualRegisterKilled(Reg, *MI); 0
1127 } ----
1128 ----
1129 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\trescheduled kill: " << *KillMI); 0
1130 return true; 0
1131 } 0
1132 ----
1133 /// Tries to commute the operand 'BaseOpIdx' and some other operand in the ----
1134 /// given machine instruction to improve opportunities for coalescing and ----
1135 /// elimination of a register to register copy. ----
1136 /// ----
1137 /// 'DstOpIdx' specifies the index of MI def operand. ----
1138 /// 'BaseOpKilled' specifies if the register associated with 'BaseOpIdx' ----
1139 /// operand is killed by the given instruction. ----
1140 /// The 'Dist' arguments provides the distance of MI from the start of the ----
1141 /// current basic block and it is used to determine if it is profitable ----
1142 /// to commute operands in the instruction. ----
1143 /// ----
1144 /// Returns true if the transformation happened. Otherwise, returns false. ----
1145 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass::tryInstructionCommute(MachineInstr *MI, 0
1146 unsigned DstOpIdx, ----
1147 unsigned BaseOpIdx, ----
1148 bool BaseOpKilled, ----
1149 unsigned Dist) { ----
1150 if (!MI->isCommutable()) 0
1151 return false; 0
1152 ----
1153 bool MadeChange = false; 0
1154 Register DstOpReg = MI->getOperand(DstOpIdx).getReg(); 0
1155 Register BaseOpReg = MI->getOperand(BaseOpIdx).getReg(); 0
1156 unsigned OpsNum = MI->getDesc().getNumOperands(); 0
1157 unsigned OtherOpIdx = MI->getDesc().getNumDefs(); 0
1158 for (; OtherOpIdx < OpsNum; OtherOpIdx++) { 0
1159 // The call of findCommutedOpIndices below only checks if BaseOpIdx ----
1160 // and OtherOpIdx are commutable, it does not really search for ----
1161 // other commutable operands and does not change the values of passed ----
1162 // variables. ----
1163 if (OtherOpIdx == BaseOpIdx || !MI->getOperand(OtherOpIdx).isReg() || 0
1164 !TII->findCommutedOpIndices(*MI, BaseOpIdx, OtherOpIdx)) 0
1165 continue; 0
1166 ----
1167 Register OtherOpReg = MI->getOperand(OtherOpIdx).getReg(); 0
1168 bool AggressiveCommute = false; 0
1169 ----
1170 // If OtherOp dies but BaseOp does not, swap the OtherOp and BaseOp ----
1171 // operands. This makes the live ranges of DstOp and OtherOp joinable. ----
1172 bool OtherOpKilled = isKilled(*MI, OtherOpReg, MRI, TII, LIS, false); 0
1173 bool DoCommute = !BaseOpKilled && OtherOpKilled; 0
1174 ----
1175 if (!DoCommute && 0
1176 isProfitableToCommute(DstOpReg, BaseOpReg, OtherOpReg, MI, Dist)) { 0
1177 DoCommute = true; 0
1178 AggressiveCommute = true; 0
1179 } ----
1180 ----
1181 // If it's profitable to commute, try to do so. ----
1182 if (DoCommute && commuteInstruction(MI, DstOpIdx, BaseOpIdx, OtherOpIdx, 0
1183 Dist)) { ----
1184 MadeChange = true; 0
1185 ++NumCommuted; 0
1186 if (AggressiveCommute) 0
1187 ++NumAggrCommuted; 0
1188 ----
1189 // There might be more than two commutable operands, update BaseOp and ----
1190 // continue scanning. ----
1191 // FIXME: This assumes that the new instruction's operands are in the ----
1192 // same positions and were simply swapped. ----
1193 BaseOpReg = OtherOpReg; 0
1194 BaseOpKilled = OtherOpKilled; 0
1195 // Resamples OpsNum in case the number of operands was reduced. This ----
1196 // happens with X86. ----
1197 OpsNum = MI->getDesc().getNumOperands(); 0
1198 } ----
1199 } ----
1200 return MadeChange; 0
1201 } ----
1202 ----
1203 /// For the case where an instruction has a single pair of tied register ----
1204 /// operands, attempt some transformations that may either eliminate the tied ----
1205 /// operands or improve the opportunities for coalescing away the register copy. ----
1206 /// Returns true if no copy needs to be inserted to untie mi's operands ----
1207 /// (either because they were untied, or because mi was rescheduled, and will ----
1208 /// be visited again later). If the shouldOnlyCommute flag is true, only ----
1209 /// instruction commutation is attempted. ----
1210 bool TwoAddressInstructionPass:: 0
1211 tryInstructionTransform(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &mi, ----
1212 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &nmi, ----
1213 unsigned SrcIdx, unsigned DstIdx, ----
1214 unsigned &Dist, bool shouldOnlyCommute) { ----
1215 if (OptLevel == CodeGenOpt::None) 0
1216 return false; 0
1217 ----
1218 MachineInstr &MI = *mi; 0
1219 Register regA = MI.getOperand(DstIdx).getReg(); 0
1220 Register regB = MI.getOperand(SrcIdx).getReg(); 0
1221 ----
1222 assert(regB.isVirtual() && "cannot make instruction into two-address form"); 0
1223 bool regBKilled = isKilled(MI, regB, MRI, TII, LIS, true); 0
1224 ----
1225 if (regA.isVirtual()) 0
1226 scanUses(regA); 0
1227 ----
1228 bool Commuted = tryInstructionCommute(&MI, DstIdx, SrcIdx, regBKilled, Dist); 0
1229 ----
1230 // If the instruction is convertible to 3 Addr, instead ----
1231 // of returning try 3 Addr transformation aggressively and ----
1232 // use this variable to check later. Because it might be better. ----
1233 // For example, we can just use `leal (%rsi,%rdi), %eax` and `ret` ----
1234 // instead of the following code. ----
1235 // addl %esi, %edi ----
1236 // movl %edi, %eax ----
1237 // ret ----
1238 if (Commuted && !MI.isConvertibleTo3Addr()) 0
1239 return false; 0
1240 ----
1241 if (shouldOnlyCommute) 0
1242 return false; 0
1243 ----
1244 // If there is one more use of regB later in the same MBB, consider ----
1245 // re-schedule this MI below it. ----
1246 if (!Commuted && EnableRescheduling && rescheduleMIBelowKill(mi, nmi, regB)) { 0
1247 ++NumReSchedDowns; 0
1248 return true; 0
1249 } ----
1250 ----
1251 // If we commuted, regB may have changed so we should re-sample it to avoid ----
1252 // confusing the three address conversion below. ----
1253 if (Commuted) { 0
1254 regB = MI.getOperand(SrcIdx).getReg(); 0
1255 regBKilled = isKilled(MI, regB, MRI, TII, LIS, true); 0
1256 } ----
1257 ----
1258 if (MI.isConvertibleTo3Addr()) { 0
1259 // This instruction is potentially convertible to a true ----
1260 // three-address instruction. Check if it is profitable. ----
1261 if (!regBKilled || isProfitableToConv3Addr(regA, regB)) { 0
1262 // Try to convert it. ----
1263 if (convertInstTo3Addr(mi, nmi, regA, regB, Dist)) { 0
1264 ++NumConvertedTo3Addr; 0
1265 return true; // Done with this instruction. 0
1266 } ----
1267 } ----
1268 } ----
1269 ----
1270 // Return if it is commuted but 3 addr conversion is failed. ----
1271 if (Commuted) 0
1272 return false; 0
1273 ----
1274 // If there is one more use of regB later in the same MBB, consider ----
1275 // re-schedule it before this MI if it's legal. ----
1276 if (EnableRescheduling && rescheduleKillAboveMI(mi, nmi, regB)) { 0
1277 ++NumReSchedUps; 0
1278 return true; 0
1279 } ----
1280 ----
1281 // If this is an instruction with a load folded into it, try unfolding ----
1282 // the load, e.g. avoid this: ----
1283 // movq %rdx, %rcx ----
1284 // addq (%rax), %rcx ----
1285 // in favor of this: ----
1286 // movq (%rax), %rcx ----
1287 // addq %rdx, %rcx ----
1288 // because it's preferable to schedule a load than a register copy. ----
1289 if (MI.mayLoad() && !regBKilled) { 0
1290 // Determine if a load can be unfolded. ----
1291 unsigned LoadRegIndex; ----
1292 unsigned NewOpc = ----
1293 TII->getOpcodeAfterMemoryUnfold(MI.getOpcode(), 0
1294 /*UnfoldLoad=*/true, ----
1295 /*UnfoldStore=*/false, ----
1296 &LoadRegIndex); ----
1297 if (NewOpc != 0) { 0
1298 const MCInstrDesc &UnfoldMCID = TII->get(NewOpc); 0
1299 if (UnfoldMCID.getNumDefs() == 1) { 0
1300 // Unfold the load. ----
1301 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "2addr: UNFOLDING: " << MI); 0
1302 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = ----
1303 TRI->getAllocatableClass( 0
1304 TII->getRegClass(UnfoldMCID, LoadRegIndex, TRI, *MF)); 0
1305 Register Reg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1306 SmallVector NewMIs; 0
1307 if (!TII->unfoldMemoryOperand(*MF, MI, Reg, 0
1308 /*UnfoldLoad=*/true, ----
1309 /*UnfoldStore=*/false, NewMIs)) { ----
1310 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "2addr: ABANDONING UNFOLD\n"); 0
1311 return false; 0
1312 } ----
1313 assert(NewMIs.size() == 2 && 0
1314 "Unfolded a load into multiple instructions!"); ----
1315 // The load was previously folded, so this is the only use. ----
1316 NewMIs[1]->addRegisterKilled(Reg, TRI); 0
1317 ----
1318 // Tentatively insert the instructions into the block so that they ----
1319 // look "normal" to the transformation logic. ----
1320 MBB->insert(mi, NewMIs[0]); 0
1321 MBB->insert(mi, NewMIs[1]); 0
1322 DistanceMap.insert(std::make_pair(NewMIs[0], Dist++)); 0
1323 DistanceMap.insert(std::make_pair(NewMIs[1], Dist)); 0
1324 ----
1325 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "2addr: NEW LOAD: " << *NewMIs[0] 0
1326 << "2addr: NEW INST: " << *NewMIs[1]); ----
1327 ----
1328 // Transform the instruction, now that it no longer has a load. ----
1329 unsigned NewDstIdx = NewMIs[1]->findRegisterDefOperandIdx(regA); 0
1330 unsigned NewSrcIdx = NewMIs[1]->findRegisterUseOperandIdx(regB); 0
1331 MachineBasicBlock::iterator NewMI = NewMIs[1]; 0
1332 bool TransformResult = ----
1333 tryInstructionTransform(NewMI, mi, NewSrcIdx, NewDstIdx, Dist, true); 0
1334 (void)TransformResult; ----
1335 assert(!TransformResult && 0
1336 "tryInstructionTransform() should return false."); ----
1337 if (NewMIs[1]->getOperand(NewSrcIdx).isKill()) { 0
1338 // Success, or at least we made an improvement. Keep the unfolded ----
1339 // instructions and discard the original. ----
1340 if (LV) { 0
1341 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
1342 if (MO.isReg() && MO.getReg().isVirtual()) { 0
1343 if (MO.isUse()) { 0
1344 if (MO.isKill()) { 0
1345 if (NewMIs[0]->killsRegister(MO.getReg())) 0
1346 LV->replaceKillInstruction(MO.getReg(), MI, *NewMIs[0]); 0
1347 else { ----
1348 assert(NewMIs[1]->killsRegister(MO.getReg()) && 0
1349 "Kill missing after load unfold!"); ----
1350 LV->replaceKillInstruction(MO.getReg(), MI, *NewMIs[1]); 0
1351 } ----
1352 } ----
1353 } else if (LV->removeVirtualRegisterDead(MO.getReg(), MI)) { 0
1354 if (NewMIs[1]->registerDefIsDead(MO.getReg())) 0
1355 LV->addVirtualRegisterDead(MO.getReg(), *NewMIs[1]); 0
1356 else { ----
1357 assert(NewMIs[0]->registerDefIsDead(MO.getReg()) && 0
1358 "Dead flag missing after load unfold!"); ----
1359 LV->addVirtualRegisterDead(MO.getReg(), *NewMIs[0]); 0
1360 } ----
1361 } ----
1362 } ----
1363 } ----
1364 LV->addVirtualRegisterKilled(Reg, *NewMIs[1]); 0
1365 } ----
1366 ----
1367 SmallVector OrigRegs; 0
1368 if (LIS) { 0
1369 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
1370 if (MO.isReg()) 0
1371 OrigRegs.push_back(MO.getReg()); 0
1372 } ----
1373 ----
1374 LIS->RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(MI); 0
1375 } ----
1376 ----
1377 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1378 DistanceMap.erase(&MI); 0
1379 ----
1380 // Update LiveIntervals. ----
1381 if (LIS) { 0
1382 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Begin(NewMIs[0]); 0
1383 MachineBasicBlock::iterator End(NewMIs[1]); 0
1384 LIS->repairIntervalsInRange(MBB, Begin, End, OrigRegs); 0
1385 } ----
1386 ----
1387 mi = NewMIs[1]; 0
1388 } else { 0
1389 // Transforming didn't eliminate the tie and didn't lead to an ----
1390 // improvement. Clean up the unfolded instructions and keep the ----
1391 // original. ----
1392 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "2addr: ABANDONING UNFOLD\n"); 0
1393 NewMIs[0]->eraseFromParent(); 0
1394 NewMIs[1]->eraseFromParent(); 0
1395 DistanceMap.erase(NewMIs[0]); 0
1396 DistanceMap.erase(NewMIs[1]); 0
1397 Dist--; 0
1398 } ----
1399 } 0
1400 } ----
1401 } ----
1402 ----
1403 return false; 0
1404 } ----

1406 // Collect tied operands of MI that need to be handled. ----

1446 // Process a list of tied MI operands that all use the same source register. ----
1447 // The tied pairs are of the form (SrcIdx, DstIdx). ----
1448 void ----
1449 TwoAddressInstructionPass::processTiedPairs(MachineInstr *MI, 0
1450 TiedPairList &TiedPairs, ----
1451 unsigned &Dist) { ----
1452 bool IsEarlyClobber = llvm::any_of(TiedPairs, [MI](auto const &TP) { 0
1453 return MI->getOperand(TP.second).isEarlyClobber(); 0
1454 }); ----
1455 ----
1456 bool RemovedKillFlag = false; 0
1457 bool AllUsesCopied = true; 0
1458 unsigned LastCopiedReg = 0; 0
1459 SlotIndex LastCopyIdx; 0
1460 Register RegB = 0; 0
1461 unsigned SubRegB = 0; 0
1462 for (auto &TP : TiedPairs) { 0
1463 unsigned SrcIdx = TP.first; 0
1464 unsigned DstIdx = TP.second; 0
1465 ----
1466 const MachineOperand &DstMO = MI->getOperand(DstIdx); 0
1467 Register RegA = DstMO.getReg(); 0
1468 ----
1469 // Grab RegB from the instruction because it may have changed if the ----
1470 // instruction was commuted. ----
1471 RegB = MI->getOperand(SrcIdx).getReg(); 0
1472 SubRegB = MI->getOperand(SrcIdx).getSubReg(); 0
1473 ----
1474 if (RegA == RegB) { 0
1475 // The register is tied to multiple destinations (or else we would ----
1476 // not have continued this far), but this use of the register ----
1477 // already matches the tied destination. Leave it. ----
1478 AllUsesCopied = false; 0
1479 continue; 0
1480 } ----
1481 LastCopiedReg = RegA; 0
1482 ----
1483 assert(RegB.isVirtual() && "cannot make instruction into two-address form"); 0
1484 ----
1485 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1486 // First, verify that we don't have a use of "a" in the instruction ----
1487 // (a = b + a for example) because our transformation will not ----
1488 // work. This should never occur because we are in SSA form. ----
1489 for (unsigned i = 0; i != MI->getNumOperands(); ++i) 0
1490 assert(i == DstIdx || 0
1491 !MI->getOperand(i).isReg() || ----
1492 MI->getOperand(i).getReg() != RegA); ----
1493 #endif ----
1494 ----
1495 // Emit a copy. ----
1496 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(*MI->getParent(), MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1497 TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), RegA); 0
1498 // If this operand is folding a truncation, the truncation now moves to the ----
1499 // copy so that the register classes remain valid for the operands. ----
1500 MIB.addReg(RegB, 0, SubRegB); 0
1501 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(RegB); 0
1502 if (SubRegB) { 0
1503 if (RegA.isVirtual()) { 0
1504 assert(TRI->getMatchingSuperRegClass(RC, MRI->getRegClass(RegA), 0
1505 SubRegB) && ----
1506 "tied subregister must be a truncation"); ----
1507 // The superreg class will not be used to constrain the subreg class. ----
1508 RC = nullptr; 0
1509 } else { ----
1510 assert(TRI->getMatchingSuperReg(RegA, SubRegB, MRI->getRegClass(RegB)) 0
1511 && "tied subregister must be a truncation"); ----
1512 } ----
1513 } ----
1514 ----
1515 // Update DistanceMap. ----
1516 MachineBasicBlock::iterator PrevMI = MI; 0
1517 --PrevMI; 0
1518 DistanceMap.insert(std::make_pair(&*PrevMI, Dist)); 0
1519 DistanceMap[MI] = ++Dist; 0
1520 ----
1521 if (LIS) { 0
1522 LastCopyIdx = LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*PrevMI).getRegSlot(); 0
1523 ----
1524 SlotIndex endIdx = ----
1525 LIS->getInstructionIndex(*MI).getRegSlot(IsEarlyClobber); 0
1526 if (RegA.isVirtual()) { 0
1527 LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(RegA); 0
1528 VNInfo *VNI = LI.getNextValue(LastCopyIdx, LIS->getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
1529 LI.addSegment(LiveRange::Segment(LastCopyIdx, endIdx, VNI)); 0
1530 for (auto &S : LI.subranges()) { 0
1531 VNI = S.getNextValue(LastCopyIdx, LIS->getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
1532 S.addSegment(LiveRange::Segment(LastCopyIdx, endIdx, VNI)); 0
1533 } ----
1534 } else { ----
1535 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(RegA)) { 0
1536 if (LiveRange *LR = LIS->getCachedRegUnit(Unit)) { 0
1537 VNInfo *VNI = ----
1538 LR->getNextValue(LastCopyIdx, LIS->getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
1539 LR->addSegment(LiveRange::Segment(LastCopyIdx, endIdx, VNI)); 0
1540 } ----
1541 } ----
1542 } ----
1543 } ----
1544 ----
1545 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tprepend:\t" << *MIB); 0
1546 ----
1547 MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(SrcIdx); 0
1548 assert(MO.isReg() && MO.getReg() == RegB && MO.isUse() && 0
1549 "inconsistent operand info for 2-reg pass"); ----
1550 if (MO.isKill()) { 0
1551 MO.setIsKill(false); 0
1552 RemovedKillFlag = true; 0
1553 } ----
